            <p>

                MCP (Model Context Protocol) is an open standard for connecting AI assistants to external tools and data sources. By adding MCP servers to Claude Code, you extend what it can reach beyond your local files &mdash; databases, issue trackers, cloud services, browsers, and more.
                Once an MCP server is connected, its tools become available to Claude Code just like the built-in ones. For example, with the right servers configured Claude can:
                <ul>
                    <li>Read and create GitHub issues and pull requests.</li>
                    <li>Query a database or an internal API.</li>
                    <li>Search email, calendars, or documents.</li>
                    <li>Drive a headless browser to test a web page.</li>
                </ul>
                You manage servers with the <code>claude mcp</code> commands (add, list, remove) or through your configuration files. Each server declares which tools it exposes, and Claude Code asks for permission before using them &mdash; so you stay in control of what external systems it can touch.

            </p>
